items.title: Polish voters set for tight presidential race after 10 years of Duda
items.description: Sunday's first-round is expected to set up a run-off between Warsaw's liberal mayor and a conservative historian.

items.title: Gabon's ousted president and family freed after two years and fly to Angola
items.description: Sylvia Bongo and her son was freed from prison last week despite facing charges of embezzling public funds.

items.title: Is there a genocide of white South Africans as Trump claims?
items.description: US President Donald Trump says a genocide is taking place in South Africa, a claim a judge dismissed as "imaginary".

items.title: Tigray party says ban threatens Ethiopia peace deal
items.description: The TPLF fought a two-year civil war against the federal government, which ended in 2022.

items.title: Ancient Indian skeleton gets a museum home six years after excavation
items.description: The skeleton had been kept in a makeshift shed since its excavation in 2019 due to bureaucratic wrangling.
